# Smart Pocket Mobile App - Environment Configuration

# ENVIRONMENT-SPECIFIC .env FILES
# ================================
# 
# This project uses variant-specific .env files:
#   - .env.development  (Development server)
#   - .env.quality      (Quality/QA server)
#   - .env.production   (Production server)
# 
# These files contain non-secret configuration (API endpoints) that can be committed to version control.
# The .env files are automatically loaded by dotenv in app.config.js based on APP_VARIANT.
# 
# SECRET CONFIGURATION (GitHub Secrets)
# ======================================
# 
# Sensitive values like API keys should be stored as GitHub Secrets:
#   - PREFILLED_API_BASEURL   (optional - overrides .env base URL)
#   - PREFILLED_API_KEY       (secret - injected at build time)
# 
# These are injected by GitHub Actions at build time and are exposed to the app via
# app.config.js's extra.PREFILLED_API_BASEURL and extra.PREFILLED_API_KEY.
# 
# PRIORITY ORDER
# ==============
# 
# When the app loads, base URL configuration is resolved in this order:
#   1. PREFILLED_API_BASEURL from GitHub Secrets (highest priority - overrides everything)
#   2. PREFILLED_API_BASEURL from .env.{variant} file
#   3. Empty string (user must enter server URL in setup screen)

# API Base URL - The Smart Pocket server URL
# Loaded from .env.{variant} files
# Can be overridden by PREFILLED_API_BASEURL from GitHub Secrets
PREFILLED_API_BASEURL=http://thursday.local:3001

# API Token - SENSITIVE - Store as GitHub Secret only
# Never commit actual tokens to .env files
# Set via PREFILLED_API_KEY in GitHub Secrets
PREFILLED_API_KEY=dev_api_key_change_me

